        <tr>
          <td style="vertical-align: top;">
            <h1 style="text-align: center;"><big>Gounki</big><br>
            </h1>
            <font face="Arial, Helvetica" size="1"><b><br>
              </b></font>Gounki is a quick racing game with some unusual
            move mechanics.&nbsp; The basic concept is simple - round
            pieces move diagonally forward, and square pieces move
            sideways or forward.&nbsp; The twist is that pieces can be
            stacked (up to a height of 3) and the stacks acquire the
            movement capability of the components.&nbsp; The goal is
            simply to get any piece to the opposite side of the board.<br>
            <br>
            Read the official <a
              href="http://rvo.pagesperso-orange.fr/gounki/en/rules.html">rules
            </a>for
            details.<br>
            <br>
            <span style="font-weight: bold;"></span><span
              style="font-weight: bold;">Robots:</span> They seem pretty
            strong, if only because the lookahead is so strange to a
            human. <br>
            <br>
          </td>
          <td style="vertical-align: top;"><img style=" width: 769px;
              height: 485px;" alt="gounki board"
              src="../images/gounki-small.jpg"><br>
          </td>
        </tr>
